detaileddescription.para: Each Node class is associated with a corresponding Model class. The Model class is responsible for the creation and class wide parametrisation of its associated Node objects.
class Model manages the thread-sorted memory pool of the model. The default constructor uses one thread as default. Use set_threads() to use more than one thread.
